  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The optimal strategy for catheter ablation of persistent atrial fibrillation is not clearly
      defined. This study investigates if Complex Fractionated Atrial Electrogram (CFAE) ablation
      in addition to pulmonary vein isolation and linear ablations improves single procedural
      success rate over a 12 month follow up period.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
